A GAUTENG police officer, his wife, and their two children were shot dead yesterday evening.The 40-year-old police constable and his family were gunned down in their home in Makau near Ga-Rankuwa in Pretoria, said police spokesman Brigadier Sabatha Mokgwabone.The suspects fled the scene in the officer&rsquo;s vehicle, which was later found abandoned in another section of the village, Mokgwabone said. The family members were declared dead on scene.The officer's children were aged 3 and 22.Police were withholding their names until all family members had been notified.The constable was stationed at the Hebron police station, he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No arrests had yet been made.The motive for the shooting was unknown. http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/gauteng-cop-family-gunned-down-in-their-home-20161207